// Synthetic m1-eval counterfactual fixture. No proprietary content.
// Stage B: reads Mid (written by stage A), writes Result (= Mid + 1). Depends on
// A running first this tick. The output channel is named `Result` (not `Out`),
// because a bare `Out` is the reserved user-function return-value keyword and
// would write the frame's return slot rather than a project channel.
Result = Mid + 1.0;
